View Image Data

Image Header

 

Image header contains following information:

  1. System source - the system of record for the Image.
  2. Image classification - the classification of the Image (Conservation Image, Other Image)
  3. Name - the name of the Image. No all Images have names. The name is also not presented for manually uploaded Images in ConservationSpace
  4. File Name - the file name of the Image
  5. Specific Image Metadata - depends on the type of the Image, e.g. for Conservation Images this is the Examination/ Treatment Phase, Spectral Range, Light Type, View Description

Image Tab

 

The Image tab presents:

  1. A view of the Image

To access more detailed information select from following tabs:

  1. Image Details - to check the all Image metadata and relationships
  2. System Data
  3. Permissions 
  4. Versions
